translated: Jönsson, Ernst Fabian, estate owner. Born November 11th, 1884 in Gammalstorp, Blekinge. First child of Member of Parliament Nils J. and Hanna Jönsson. Married to Anna Nilsson for 11 years. They have 5 children: Hanna born in 1912, Nils-Erik in 1914, Inge in 1918, Karl-Axel in 1920, and Ivar in 1926. Studied at secondary school and agricultural college. Owner of the estate Gammalstorp since 1914. Chairman of the road district of Gammalstorp from 1918 to 1933, the Listers road district from 1934, household committee since 1940, municipal meeting from 1918, tax commission since 1928, property tax preparation committee in three parishes, municipal councilor since 1936, and member of the election board. Member of Gammalstorps shooting and sports association board, member of the school board, member of the crisis management board and household association management committee, chairman and member of the board of Gammalstorps and Ysane Savings Bank, member of the board of Swedish distilleries association and its executive committee, and member of some other agricultural associations. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa.
